# Observability & Resilience

## Request correlation (already in API)

Mutating controllers pass `String(req.id ?? '')` into services/audit (checkout, articles, writer-payments, auth). `ApiExceptionFilter` echoes `requestId` in every error envelope. **Keep propagating it** on new money/publish/payout paths.

```typescript
// ✅
return this.payments.release(id, user.id, String(req.id ?? ''));

// audit.write({ …, requestId })
```

## Health (platform)

| Route | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `GET /api/v1/health` | Liveness `{ status: 'ok' }` |
| `GET /api/v1/ready` | DB + Redis checks; **503** when degraded |
| `GET /api/v1/version` | Build/name metadata |

Don’t use liveness as a substitute for readiness in orchestrators.

## Logging

- Prefer structured logs; include `requestId` / stable domain `code` on failures.
- **Never** log: tokens, passwords, OTPs, PAN/CVV, raw provider payloads, full `.env`.
- Audit privileged actions via `AuditService` (`article.published`, `writer_payment.released`, …) — not only `console.log`.

## Resilience classes

| Class | HTTP | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Presentation | 400 | Bad Zod / empty cart |
| AuthZ | 401/403 | Missing JWT / `MEDICAL_GATE_REQUIRED` |
| Domain conflict | 409 (or mapped 400 with code) | Illegal status jump / `NOT_PENDING` |
| Infra | 5xx / queue retry | DB/Redis/payment timeout |

Timeouts on external calls. Retry only idempotent ops. Degrade search/recs — never “succeed” checkout on unknown payment state. No empty `catch`.
